Proceeding as in the hint, we have

$\det(A-I\lambda)
= \det\left( \begin{bmatrix}
0 & 1  \\
1 & 0  
\end{bmatrix}
-\begin{bmatrix}
\lambda & 0  \\
0 & \lambda  
\end{bmatrix}
\right)
= \det\left( \begin{bmatrix}
-\lambda & 1  \\
1 & -\lambda  
\end{bmatrix}
\right)
= \lambda^{2}-1 = (\lambda-1)(\lambda+1)$

and so the eigenvalues are given by $\lambda = \pm1$
